cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of deep neural networks, specifically those with ReLU activation functions, using gradient descent and stochastic gradient descent. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses binary classification, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep neural networks for image classification is also mentioned, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the empirical loss function and local curvature properties, which are related to optimization and could fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
